result.execSummary:
The defendant Ron Edwin Didriksen was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Ron Edwin Didriksen is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Ron Edwin Didriksen was found guilty of Battery, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).
  • Ron Edwin Didriksen was found guilty of Criminal Damage to Property, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: If probation or extended supervision is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant and in favor of restitution victims and governmental entities for the balance due.  Collections may include income assignment.  This applies to all counts and financial obligations.

Obey all of the rules and regulations of supervising probation agent. 
**Pay supervision fees.**
Do not possess or consume alcoholic beverages and do not have alcoholic beverages within the residence. Do not be in taverns or on any premises licensed for the sale of intoxicating beverages, except restaurants or grocery stores. Do not possess or consume controlled substances, except by prescription. Submit voluntarily to random tests of blood, breath or urine. Participate in counseling deemed appropriate by your agent, which may include: alcohol/drug, anger management/DV counseling, psychiatric/psychological, AODA Assessment and follow-through with recommended treatment. Actively search for employment, be employed or attend an educational institution or vocational training program. 
**Pay supervision fees.**
**If unpaid financial obligations remain at discharge or revocation, civil judgment to be entered.**
**Defendant is ordered to submit to a DNA sample & pay the surcharge, notice given to def. in court.**
May not have contact with Skyler Didricksen. May not possess any weapons, including firearms. Any violations of probation shall be reported to the Court within 30 days and at least 30 days prior to the termination of the 30 days of the DE's probation.

10:00 AM Attorney Drew Lehman in court for State of Wisconsin. Defendant Ron Edwin Didriksen in court.  Attorney Michael D. Cicchini in court for Ron Edwin Didriksen. Clerk N. Nobile.
MINUTES: Victim rights compliance. Matter is resolved and agreement is placed on the record. On motion of the State Domestic Abuse enhancers are stricken from counts 2 and 3. Defendant entered a plea of guilty to amended counts 2-3; found guilty by the court. On State's motion, counts 1 and 4 are dismissed. Court orders withheld sentence; defendant placed on probation for 12 months w/conditions. No contact with Skylar D.. Any violation of probation shall be reported to the Court within 30 days and at least 30 days prior to the termination of the DE's probation. 1 day sentence credit if revoked.  Court costs and DNA surcharge ordered.  Defendant is ordered to submit a DNA sample; written notice provided to defendant. Court finds DE is eligible for expunction and will schedule an expunction hearing. Court will grant expunction upon successful completion of probation.
Hearing scheduled for October 2, 2023 at 01:30 pm.
